<section class="block-section story">
  <span class="section-tag">📖 Story</span>
  <h2>Why this block matters</h2>
  <p class="sub">The design move: allocate the grid, and watch every objective respond.</p>
  <p>You allocate your neighbourhood grid across 8 urban land uses (residential, mixed-use, commercial and markets, civic and services, green space, blue space, streets and mobility, and existing fabric and informal settlements), and they must add up to the whole area. The planned <strong>Land Allocation Optimizer</strong> lets you see seven objective scores move in real time as you redesign, and the Pareto frontier lights up where you hit a real trade-off. There is no allocation that wins on every objective, which is exactly the design reasoning this unit teaches. The two AI partners enter here: the <a href="/ai-partners/urban-planner/">Urban Planner</a> pushes density and housing supply, the <a href="/ai-partners/equity-resilience-partner/">Equity &amp; Resilience Partner</a> pushes green-blue space and protection from displacement, flood, and heat. Your job is to synthesise their disagreement, not to pick one and ignore the other.</p>
  <p class="sub" style="color: var(--muted);">Full block content lands in the Unit 6 deep build. The Land Allocation Optimizer is still in development (see the <a href="/reference/simulator-hub/">simulator hub</a>).</p>
</section>

